1992.assessment:
Sanctions era begins; continued repression of southern Shia population;
military operations in Shia marshlands; no-fly zones enforced; low-level
Kurdish insurgency.

1993.assessment:
State repression continues; marsh draining operations targeting Marsh Arabs;
political executions; limited armed opposition activity; US cruise missile
strikes (June) minimal casualties.

2004.assessment:
Insurgency escalates dramatically; Fallujah battles (April, November); Mahdi
Army uprising (April-August); widespread IED attacks; foreign fighter influx;
Abu Ghraib scandal; sectarian violence accelerates.

2005.assessment:
Intense insurgent violence; elections spark sectarian attacks (Jan, Oct, Dec);
al-Qaeda in Iraq expands; suicide bombings escalate; Tal Afar operation;
sectarian displacement begins; death squads active.

2007.assessment:
Surge operations begin (Jan); continued high sectarian violence first half;
Anbar Awakening reduces Sunni insurgency; violence declining second half but
still severe; massive displacement continues.

2021.assessment:
ISIS insurgency continues with rural attacks; US combat mission ends (July);
PMF rocket and drone attacks on US interests; elections (October) with low
turnout; violence declining trend continues. IBC ~2,000 civilian deaths.

2020.assessment:
Journalist and activist assassinations continue. Soleimani killing aftermath;
US-Iran conflict restricts press freedom. COVID-19 restrictions. Continued
activist journalist killings by unidentified armed groups. RSF raw ~74.
